      "role": "user",
      "content": "i see. so if that's a primary reason, wouldn't that mean that expanding these programs is actually counterproductive for the economy in the long run since it keeps people out of the workforce? it seems like a pretty clear case of a trade-off where the social cost is higher than the benefit.",
